headline.main: FEAR NEW BLOW FROM LEASE-LEND; Traders Get Copy of Plan for British Warehouse, Inland Freight Control

lead_paragraph: Fears that the loss of foreign freight handling resulting from lease-lend transactions with the British would spread to domestic warehousing and shipping of products destined for Britain, were heightened yesterday with the disclosure by foreign freight forwarders here of a memorandum by a government official which outlines a proposed extension of existing practices.
abstract: Maj Gen J H Burns' memo to House com showing U S War Dept Defense Aid Stations and Forecast-Movements-Storage Office plans feared as blow to private warehousing
